{
  "texts": [
    "Parsing the answer can generate additional questions, resulting in a 'conversation' about the text input.",
    "In Fig. 2, questions are about causes and consequences, and the answers are parsed to isolate concepts.",
    "While such systems are increasingly familiar in e-commerce platforms (Du et al., 2023), there is also a growing interest in using them to identify relations (Yan et al., 2021).",
    "The introduction of accessible and disruptive technology such as generative AI has allowed to create GPT-based Q&A systems (Omar et al., 2023).",
    "The literature reports mixed findings, as some authors noted that GPT-3.5 outperforms well-known models such as ChatGPT and T5 on causal questions (Tan et al., 2023), while others observed that GPT-3.5 models only \"have outstanding performance and robustness for some specific relational judgments\" found in common expressions (Chen et al., 2023)."
  ]
}